      "content": "hey i keep getting heap growth issues in this small embedded project. i use a simple class to manage some sensor data but the memory just keeps climbing. can u look at this and tell me why it's leaking?\n\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\n\nclass SensorData {\npublic:\n    SensorData(int id) : sensorId(id) {\n        data = new float[100];\n        std::cout << \"Sensor \" << sensorId << \" initialized\" << std::endl;\n    }\n    ~SensorData() {\n        std::cout << \"Sensor \" << sensorId << \" destroyed\" << std::endl;\n    }\n    void process() { /* some logic */ }\n\nprivate:\n    int sensorId;\n    float* data;\n};\n\nvoid runSystem() {\n    for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {\n        SensorData* s = new SensorData(i);\n        s->process();\n        // i think i'm doing it right but it's still growing\n    }\n}\n\nint main() {\n    runSystem();\n    return 0;\n}\n```",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
